      "name": "Authentic Kung Pao Chicken (Gong Bao Ji Ding)",
      "instructions": [
        "Cut the chicken breasts into 1.5cm cubes. Marinate with 1 tsp of light soy sauce, 1 tsp of Shaoxing rice wine, and 1 tsp of cornstarch for 15 minutes.",
        "Prepare the sauce by mixing Chinkiang vinegar, sugar, remaining light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, remaining cornstarch, and 1 tbsp of water in a small bowl.",
        "Cut the spring onions into 1.5cm white and light green sections. Finely slice the garlic and ginger.",
        "Heat cooking oil in a wok over medium-low heat. Add dried red chilies and Sichuan peppercorns, frying until fragrant and slightly darkened, being careful not to burn them.",
        "Add the marinated chicken cubes, turn up the heat to high, and stir-fry until the chicken turns white.",
        "Toss in the ginger, garlic, and spring onion sections, stir-frying for 1 minute until fragrant.",
        "Pour in the prepared sauce, stirring quickly to coat the chicken as the sauce thickens.",
        "Stir in the peanuts, give it a final toss, and serve immediately."
